The paper discusses the use of deep learning approaches for speech recognition in non-stationary acoustic environments. This topic falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science, including signal processing (cs.SD), natural language processing (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
